# @eproject/components — Project Context

This is a **React component library** (not an app) built with:
- React 19 + TypeScript 5.9
- Apache ECharts 6 for chart rendering
- Vite 8 in library mode (outputs ESM + CJS to `dist/`)
- Storybook 10 for component previews

## Key architecture

- `BaseChart.tsx` is the low-level ECharts wrapper — avoid modifying it
- All chart components (LineChart, BarChart, PieChart, etc.) wrap `BaseChart`
- Each chart exposes only simple, readable props (title, data, colors, variant)
- ECharts `option` objects are built inside `useMemo` from those props
- `src/utils/theme.ts` holds shared defaults (colors, variant layout presets)
- `src/types/chart.ts` holds shared TypeScript types

## Export structure

- `src/index.ts` → main entry, re-exports everything from `src/components/`
- Every new component must be exported from `src/components/charts/index.ts`

## Commands

- `npm run dev` — starts Storybook on port 6006
- `npm run build` — builds the library to `dist/`
- `npm run lint` — TypeScript type check
